523 inline intptr_t ConvertErrnoToLinux(auto err)
524 {
525  intptr_t errc = (intptr_t)err;
526 
527  if (errc >= 0)
528  {
529  debug("no change for %#lx", errc);
530  return errc;
531  }
532 
533  intptr_t ret = errnoMap[-errc];
534  debug("converted %s(%ld) to %s(%ld)", nErrnoStr[-errc], -errc, lErrnoStr[ret], ret);
535  return -ret;
536 }
537 
538 int ConvertSignalToLinux(Signals sig)
539 {
540  if (sig >= SIGRTMIN && sig <= SIGRTMAX)
541  return sig; /* We ignore for now */
542 
543  foreach (auto &mapping in signalMapping)
544  {
545  if (mapping.nativeSignal == sig)
546  {
547  // debug("Converted \"%s\"(%d) to \"%s\"(%d)",
548  // sigStr[mapping.nativeSignal], sig,
549  // lSigStr[mapping.linuxSignal], mapping.linuxSignal);
550  return mapping.linuxSignal;
551  }
552  }
553  debug("Unknown signal %d", sig);
554  // assert(!"Unknown signal");
555  return SIG_NULL;
556 }
557 
558 Signals ConvertSignalToNative(int sig)
559 {
560  if (sig >= linux_SIGRTMIN && sig <= linux_SIGRTMAX)
561  return (Signals)sig; /* We ignore for now */
562 
563  foreach (auto &mapping in signalMapping)
564  {
565  if (mapping.linuxSignal == sig)
566  {
567  // debug("Converted \"%s\"(%d) to \"%s\"(%d)",
568  // lSigStr[mapping.linuxSignal], sig,
569  // sigStr[mapping.nativeSignal], mapping.nativeSignal);
570  return mapping.nativeSignal;
571  }
572  }
573  debug("Unknown signal %d", sig);
574  // assert(!"Unknown signal");
575  return SIG_NULL;
576 }
577 
578 unsigned long ConvertMaskToNative(unsigned long mask)
579 {
580  unsigned long ret = 0;
581  for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++)
582  {
583  if (mask & (1ul << i))
584  {
585  int sig = ConvertSignalToNative(i + 1);
586  if (unlikely(sig == SIG_NULL))
587  continue;
588  ret |= 1ul << (sig - 1);
589  }
590  }
591  return ret;
592 
593  // std::bitset<SIGNAL_MAX + 1> bitMask(mask);
594  // for (int i = 0; i < SIGNAL_MAX + 1; i++)
595  // {
596  // if (bitMask.test(i))
597  // ret |= 1 << (ConvertSignalToNative(i + 1) - 1);
598  // }
599 }
600 
601 unsigned long ConvertMaskToLinux(unsigned long mask)
602 {
603  unsigned long ret = 0;
604  for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++)
605  {
606  if (mask & (1ul << i))
607  {
608  int sig = ConvertSignalToLinux((Signals)(i + 1));
609  if (unlikely(sig == SIG_NULL))
610  continue;
611  ret |= 1ul << (sig - 1);
612  }
613  }
614  return ret;
615 
616  // std::bitset<linux_SIGUNUSED + 1> bitMask(mask);
617  // for (int i = 0; i < linux_SIGUNUSED + 1; i++)
618  // {
619  // if (bitMask.test(i))
620  // ret |= 1 << (ConvertSignalToLinux(i + 1) - 1);
621  // }
622 }
623 
624 void SetSigActToNative(const k_sigaction *linux, SignalAction *native)
625 {
626  native->sa_handler.Handler = linux->handler;
627  native->Flags = linux->flags;
628  native->Restorer = linux->restorer;
629 
630  unsigned long mask = ((unsigned long)linux->mask[1] << 32) | linux->mask[0];
631  native->Mask = std::bitset<64>(ConvertMaskToNative(mask));
632  debug("m0:%#lx m1:%#lx | n:%#lx", linux->mask[0], linux->mask[1], native->Mask);
633 }
634 
635 void SetSigActToLinux(const SignalAction *native, k_sigaction *linux)
636 {
637  linux->handler = native->sa_handler.Handler;
638  linux->flags = native->Flags;
639  linux->restorer = native->Restorer;
640 
641  unsigned long mask = native->Mask.to_ulong();
642  mask = ConvertMaskToLinux(mask);
643 
644  linux->mask[0] = mask & 0xFFFFFFFF;
645  linux->mask[1] = (uint32_t)((mask >> 32) & 0xFFFFFFFF);
646  debug("m0:%#lx m1:%#lx | n:%#lx", linux->mask[0], linux->mask[1], native->Mask);
647 }
648 
649 struct kstat KStatToStat(struct linux_kstat linux_stat)
650 {
651  struct kstat stat;
652  stat.Device = linux_stat.st_dev;
653  stat.Index = linux_stat.st_ino;
654  stat.HardLinks = (nlink_t)linux_stat.st_nlink;
655  stat.Mode = linux_stat.st_mode;
656  stat.UserID = linux_stat.st_uid;
657  stat.GroupID = linux_stat.st_gid;
658  stat.RawDevice = linux_stat.st_rdev;
659  stat.Size = linux_stat.st_size;
660  stat.BlockSize = linux_stat.st_blksize;
661  stat.Blocks = linux_stat.st_blocks;
662  stat.AccessTime = linux_stat.st_atime;
663  // stat.st_atime_nsec = linux_stat.st_atime_nsec;
664  stat.ModifyTime = linux_stat.st_mtime;
665  // stat.st_mtime_nsec = linux_stat.st_mtime_nsec;
666  stat.ChangeTime = linux_stat.st_ctime;
667  // stat.st_ctime_nsec = linux_stat.st_ctime_nsec;
668  return stat;
669 }
670 
671 struct linux_kstat StatToKStat(struct kstat stat)
672 {
673  struct linux_kstat linux_stat;
674  linux_stat.st_dev = stat.Device;
675  linux_stat.st_ino = stat.Index;
676  linux_stat.st_nlink = stat.HardLinks;
677  linux_stat.st_mode = stat.Mode;
678  linux_stat.st_uid = stat.UserID;
679  linux_stat.st_gid = stat.GroupID;
680  linux_stat.st_rdev = stat.RawDevice;
681  linux_stat.st_size = stat.Size;
682  linux_stat.st_blksize = stat.BlockSize;
683  linux_stat.st_blocks = stat.Blocks;
684  linux_stat.st_atime = stat.AccessTime;
685  // linux_stat.st_atime_nsec = stat.st_atime_nsec;
686  linux_stat.st_mtime = stat.ModifyTime;
687  // linux_stat.st_mtime_nsec = stat.st_mtime_nsec;
688  linux_stat.st_ctime = stat.ChangeTime;
689  // linux_stat.st_ctime_nsec = stat.st_ctime_nsec;
690  return linux_stat;
691 }

693 struct kstat OKStatToStat(struct __old_kernel_stat okstat)
694 {
695  struct kstat stat;
696  stat.Device = okstat.st_dev;
697  stat.Index = okstat.st_ino;
698  stat.HardLinks = okstat.st_nlink;
699  stat.Mode = okstat.st_mode;
700  stat.UserID = okstat.st_uid;
701  stat.GroupID = okstat.st_gid;
702  stat.RawDevice = okstat.st_rdev;
703  stat.Size = okstat.st_size;
704  stat.AccessTime = okstat.st_atime;
705  stat.ModifyTime = okstat.st_mtime;
706  stat.ChangeTime = okstat.st_ctime;
707  return stat;
708 }

710 struct __old_kernel_stat StatToOKStat(struct kstat stat)
711 {
712  struct __old_kernel_stat okstat;
713  okstat.st_dev = (unsigned short)stat.Device;
714  okstat.st_ino = (unsigned short)stat.Index;
715  okstat.st_nlink = (unsigned short)stat.HardLinks;
716  okstat.st_mode = (unsigned short)stat.Mode;
717  okstat.st_uid = (unsigned short)stat.UserID;
718  okstat.st_gid = (unsigned short)stat.GroupID;
719  okstat.st_rdev = (unsigned short)stat.RawDevice;
720 #ifdef __i386__
721  okstat.st_size = (unsigned long)stat.Size;
722  okstat.st_atime = (unsigned long)stat.AccessTime;
723  okstat.st_mtime = (unsigned long)stat.ModifyTime;
724  okstat.st_ctime = (unsigned long)stat.ChangeTime;
725 #else
726  okstat.st_size = (unsigned int)stat.Size;
727  okstat.st_atime = (unsigned int)stat.AccessTime;
728  okstat.st_mtime = (unsigned int)stat.ModifyTime;
729  okstat.st_ctime = (unsigned int)stat.ChangeTime;
730 #endif
731  return okstat;
732 }

734 __no_stack_protector void __LinuxForkReturn(void *tableAddr)
735 {
736 #if defined(a64)
737  asmv("movq %0, %%cr3" ::"r"(tableAddr)); /* Load process page table */
738  asmv("movq $0, %rax\n"); /* Return 0 */
739  asmv("movq %r8, %rsp\n"); /* Restore stack pointer */
740  asmv("movq %r8, %rbp\n"); /* Restore base pointer */
741  asmv("swapgs\n"); /* Swap GS back to the user GS */
742  asmv("sti\n"); /* Enable interrupts */
743  asmv("sysretq\n"); /* Return to rcx address in user mode */
744 #elif defined(a32)
745 #warning "__LinuxForkReturn not implemented for i386"
746 #endif
747  __builtin_unreachable();
748 }

750 static ssize_t linux_read(SysFrm *, int fd, void *buf, size_t count)
751 {
752  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
753  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
754 
755  void *pBuf = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(buf, count);
756  if (pBuf == nullptr)
757  return -linux_EFAULT;
758 
759  func("%d, %p, %d", fd, buf, count);
760 
761  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
762  ssize_t ret = ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->usr_read(fd, pBuf, count));
763  if (ret >= 0)
764  fdt->usr_lseek(fd, ret, SEEK_CUR);
765 
766 #ifdef DEBUG
767  DumpData("READ", pBuf, ret < 0 ? 0 : ret);
768 #endif
769  return ret;
770 }
771 
772 static ssize_t linux_write(SysFrm *, int fd, const void *buf, size_t count)
773 {
774  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
775  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
776 
777  const void *pBuf = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(buf, count);
778  if (pBuf == nullptr)
779  return -linux_EFAULT;
780 
781  func("%d, %p, %d", fd, buf, count);
782 
783  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
784  ssize_t ret = ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->usr_write(fd, pBuf, count));
785  if (ret)
786  fdt->usr_lseek(fd, ret, SEEK_CUR);
787 
788 #ifdef DEBUG
789  DumpData("WRITE", (void *)pBuf, ret < 0 ? 0 : ret);
790 #endif
791  return ret;
792 }

794 static int linux_open(SysFrm *sf, const char *pathname, int flags, mode_t mode)
795 {
796  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
797  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
798 
799  const char *pPathname = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(pathname, PAGE_SIZE);
800  if (pPathname == nullptr)
801  return -linux_EFAULT;
802 
803  func("%s, %d, %d", pPathname, flags, mode);
804 
805  if (flags & 0200000 /* O_DIRECTORY */)
806  {
807  FileNode *node = fs->GetByPath(pPathname, pcb->CWD);
808  if (node == nullptr)
809  {
810  debug("Couldn't find %s", pPathname);
811  return -linux_ENOENT;
812  }
813 
814  if (!node->IsDirectory())
815  {
816  debug("%s is not a directory", pPathname);
817  return -linux_ENOTDIR;
818  }
819  }
820 
821  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
822  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->usr_open(pPathname, flags, mode));
823 }

827  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;

829  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->usr_close(fd));

837 static int linux_stat(SysFrm *, const char *pathname, struct linux_kstat *statbuf)
838 {
839  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
840  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
841  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
842 
843  auto pPathname = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(pathname, PAGE_SIZE);
844  if (pPathname == nullptr)
845  return -linux_EFAULT;
846 
847  auto pStatbuf = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(statbuf);
848  if (pStatbuf == nullptr)
849  return -linux_EFAULT;
850 
851  struct kstat nstat = KStatToStat(*pStatbuf);
852  int ret = ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->usr_stat(pPathname, &nstat));
853  *pStatbuf = StatToKStat(nstat);
854  return ret;
855 }

873 static int linux_lstat(SysFrm *, const char *pathname, struct linux_kstat *statbuf)

886  *pStatbuf = StatToKStat(nstat);

892 static off_t linux_lseek(SysFrm *, int fd, off_t offset, int whence)
893 {
894  static_assert(linux_SEEK_SET == SEEK_SET);
895  static_assert(linux_SEEK_CUR == SEEK_CUR);
896  static_assert(linux_SEEK_END == SEEK_END);
897 
898  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
899  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
900  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->usr_lseek(fd, offset, whence));
901 }
902 
903 static void *linux_mmap(SysFrm *, void *addr, size_t length, int prot,
904  int flags, int fildes, off_t offset)
905 {
906  if (length == 0)
907  return (void *)-linux_EINVAL;
908 
909  bool p_None = prot & linux_PROT_NONE;
910  bool p_Read = prot & linux_PROT_READ;
911  bool p_Write = prot & linux_PROT_WRITE;
912  bool p_Exec = prot & linux_PROT_EXEC;
913 
914  bool m_Shared = flags & linux_MAP_SHARED;
915  bool m_Private = flags & linux_MAP_PRIVATE;
916  bool m_Fixed = flags & linux_MAP_FIXED;
917  bool m_Anon = flags & linux_MAP_ANONYMOUS;
918 
919  UNUSED(p_None);
920  UNUSED(m_Anon);
921 
922  debug("None:%d Read:%d Write:%d Exec:%d",
923  p_None, p_Read, p_Write, p_Exec);
924 
925  debug("Shared:%d Private:%d Fixed:%d Anon:%d",
926  m_Shared, m_Private, m_Fixed, m_Anon);
927 
928  int unknownFlags = flags & ~(linux_MAP_SHARED | linux_MAP_PRIVATE |
929  linux_MAP_FIXED | linux_MAP_ANONYMOUS);
930  if (unknownFlags)
931  {
932  /* We still have some flags missing afaik... */
933  fixme("Unknown flags: %x", unknownFlags);
934  /* FIXME: Continue? */
935  }
936 
937  if (offset % PAGE_SIZE)
938  return (void *)-linux_EINVAL;
939 
940  if (uintptr_t(addr) % PAGE_SIZE && m_Fixed)
941  return (void *)-linux_EINVAL;
942 
943  if ((m_Shared && m_Private) ||
944  (!m_Shared && !m_Private))
945  return (void *)-linux_EINVAL;
946 
947  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
948  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
949  if (fildes != -1 && !m_Anon)
950  {
951  fixme("File mapping not fully implemented");
952  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
953 
954  auto _fd = fdt->FileMap.find(fildes);
955  if (_fd == fdt->FileMap.end())
956  {
957  debug("Invalid file descriptor %d", fildes);
958  return (void *)-linux_EBADF;
959  }
960 
961  if (p_Read)
962  {
963  void *pBuf = vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(length));
964  debug("created buffer at %#lx-%#lx",
965  pBuf, (uintptr_t)pBuf + length);
966 
967  uintptr_t mFlags = Memory::US;
968  if (p_Write)
969  mFlags |= Memory::RW;
970 
971  if (m_Fixed)
972  {
973  if (m_Shared)
974  return (void *)-linux_ENOSYS;
975 
976  int mRet = vma->Map(addr, pBuf, length, mFlags);
977  if (mRet < 0)
978  {
979  debug("Failed to map file: %s", strerror(mRet));
980  return (void *)(uintptr_t)ConvertErrnoToLinux(mRet);
981  }
982  off_t oldOff = fdt->usr_lseek(fildes, 0, SEEK_CUR);
983  fdt->usr_lseek(fildes, offset, SEEK_SET);
984 
985  ssize_t ret = fdt->usr_read(fildes, pBuf, length);
986  fdt->usr_lseek(fildes, oldOff, SEEK_SET);
987 
988  if (ret < 0)
989  {
990  debug("Failed to read file");
991  return (void *)ConvertErrnoToLinux(ret);
992  }
993  return addr;
994  }
995  else
996  {
997  int mRet = vma->Map(pBuf, pBuf, length, mFlags);
998  if (mRet < 0)
999  {
1000  debug("Failed to map file: %s", strerror(mRet));
1001  return (void *)(uintptr_t)ConvertErrnoToLinux(mRet);
1002  }
1003  }
1004 
1005  off_t oldOff = fdt->usr_lseek(fildes, 0, SEEK_CUR);
1006  fdt->usr_lseek(fildes, offset, SEEK_SET);
1007 
1008  ssize_t ret = fdt->usr_read(fildes, pBuf, length);
1009 
1010  fdt->usr_lseek(fildes, oldOff, SEEK_SET);
1011 
1012  if (ret < 0)
1013  {
1014  debug("Failed to read file");
1015  return (void *)ConvertErrnoToLinux(ret);
1016  }
1017  return pBuf;
1018  }
1019 
1020  debug("???");
1021  return (void *)-linux_ENOSYS;
1022  }
1023 
1024  void *ret = vma->CreateCoWRegion(addr, length,
1025  p_Read, p_Write, p_Exec,
1026  m_Fixed, m_Shared);
1027  debug("ret: %#lx", ret);
1028  return (void *)ret;
1029 }
1030 #undef __FENNIX_KERNEL_SYSCALLS_LIST_H__
1031 
1032 static int linux_mprotect(SysFrm *, void *addr, size_t len, int prot)
1033 {
1034  if (len == 0)
1035  return -linux_EINVAL;
1036 
1037  if (uintptr_t(addr) % PAGE_SIZE)
1038  return -linux_EINVAL;
1039 
1040  // bool p_None = prot & linux_PROT_NONE;
1041  bool p_Read = prot & linux_PROT_READ;
1042  bool p_Write = prot & linux_PROT_WRITE;
1043  // bool p_Exec = prot & linux_PROT_EXEC;
1044 
1045  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1046  Memory::Virtual vmm = Memory::Virtual(pcb->PageTable);
1047 
1048  for (uintptr_t i = uintptr_t(addr);
1049  i < uintptr_t(addr) + len;
1050  i += PAGE_SIZE)
1051  {
1052  if (unlikely(vmm.Check((void *)i, Memory::G)))
1053  {
1054  warn("%p is a global page", (void *)i);
1055  return -linux_ENOMEM;
1056  }
1057 
1058  Memory::PageTableEntry *pte = vmm.GetPTE(addr);
1059  if (pte == nullptr)
1060  {
1061  debug("Page %#lx is not mapped inside %#lx",
1062  (void *)i, pcb->PageTable);
1063  fixme("Page %#lx is not mapped", (void *)i);
1064  continue;
1065  return -linux_ENOMEM;
1066  }
1067 
1068  if (!pte->Present ||
1069  (!pte->UserSupervisor && p_Read) ||
1070  (!pte->ReadWrite && p_Write))
1071  {
1072  debug("Page %p is not mapped with the correct permissions",
1073  (void *)i);
1074  return -linux_EACCES;
1075  }
1076 
1077  // pte->Present = !p_None;
1078  pte->UserSupervisor = p_Read;
1079  pte->ReadWrite = p_Write;
1080  // pte->ExecuteDisable = p_Exec;
1081 
1082  debug("Changed permissions of page %#lx to %s %s %s %s",
1083  (void *)i,
1084  (prot & linux_PROT_NONE) ? "None" : "",
1085  p_Read ? "Read" : "",
1086  p_Write ? "Write" : "",
1087  (prot & linux_PROT_EXEC) ? "Exec" : "");
1088 
1089 #if defined(a64)
1090  CPU::x64::invlpg(addr);
1091 #elif defined(a32)
1092  CPU::x32::invlpg(addr);
1093 #elif defined(aa64)
1094  asmv("dsb sy");
1095  asmv("tlbi vae1is, %0"
1096  :
1097  : "r"(addr)
1098  : "memory");
1099  asmv("dsb sy");
1100  asmv("isb");
1101 #endif
1102  }
1103 
1104  return 0;
1105 }

1107 static int linux_munmap(SysFrm *, void *addr, size_t length)
1108 {
1109  if (uintptr_t(addr) % PAGE_SIZE)
1110  return -linux_EINVAL;
1111 
1112  if (length == 0)
1113  return -linux_EINVAL;
1114 
1115  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1116  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
1117  vma->FreePages((void *)addr, TO_PAGES(length));
1118  return 0;
1119 }

1177 static ssize_t linux_readv(SysFrm *sf, int fildes, const struct iovec *iov, int iovcnt)
1178 {
1179  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1180  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
1181 
1182  const struct iovec *pIov = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(iov, sizeof(struct iovec) * iovcnt);
1183  if (pIov == nullptr)
1184  return -linux_EFAULT;
1185 
1186  ssize_t Total = 0;
1187  for (int i = 0; i < iovcnt; i++)
1188  {
1189  debug("%d: iov[%d]: %p %d", fildes, i, pIov[i].iov_base, pIov[i].iov_len);
1190 
1191  if (!pIov[i].iov_base)
1192  {
1193  debug("invalid iov_base");
1194  return -linux_EFAULT;
1195  }
1196 
1197  if (pIov[i].iov_len == 0)
1198  {
1199  debug("invalid iov_len");
1200  continue;
1201  }
1202 
1203  ssize_t n = linux_read(sf, fildes, pIov[i].iov_base, pIov[i].iov_len);
1204  if (n < 0)
1205  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(n);
1206  debug("n: %d", n);
1207 
1208  Total += n;
1209  if (n < (ssize_t)pIov[i].iov_len)
1210  {
1211  debug("break");
1212  break;
1213  }
1214  }
1215  debug("readv: %d", Total);
1216  return Total;
1217 }
1218 
1219 static ssize_t linux_writev(SysFrm *sf, int fildes, const struct iovec *iov, int iovcnt)

1228  ssize_t Total = 0;

1230  {

1232 
1233  if (!pIov[i].iov_base)
1234  {
1235  debug("invalid iov_base");
1236  return -linux_EFAULT;
1237  }
1238 
1239  if (pIov[i].iov_len == 0)
1240  {

1320 static int linux_nanosleep(SysFrm *,
1321  const struct timespec *req,
1322  struct timespec *rem)
1323 {
1324  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1325  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
1326 
1327  auto pReq = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(req);
1328  auto pRem = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(rem);
1329  if (pReq == nullptr || pRem == nullptr)
1330  return -linux_EFAULT;
1331 
1332  if (pReq->tv_nsec < 0 || pReq->tv_nsec > 999999999)
1333  {
1334  debug("Invalid tv_nsec %ld", pReq->tv_nsec);
1335  return -linux_EINVAL;
1336  }
1337 
1338  if (pReq->tv_sec < 0)
1339  {
1340  debug("Invalid tv_sec %ld", pReq->tv_sec);
1341  return -linux_EINVAL;
1342  }
1343 
1344  debug("tv_nsec=%ld tv_sec=%ld",
1345  pReq->tv_nsec, pReq->tv_sec);
1346 
1347  uint64_t nanoTime = pReq->tv_nsec;
1348  uint64_t secTime = pReq->tv_sec * 1000000000; /* Nano */
1349 
1350  uint64_t time = TimeManager->GetCounter();
1351  uint64_t sleepTime = TimeManager->CalculateTarget(nanoTime + secTime, Time::Nanoseconds);
1352 
1353  debug("time=%ld secTime=%ld nanoTime=%ld sleepTime=%ld",
1354  time, secTime, nanoTime, sleepTime);
1355 
1356  while (time < sleepTime)
1357  {
1358  if (pcb->Signals.HasPendingSignal())
1359  {
1360  debug("sleep interrupted by signal");
1361  return -linux_EINTR;
1362  }
1363 
1364  pcb->GetContext()->Yield();
1365  time = TimeManager->GetCounter();
1366  }
1367  debug("time= %ld", time);
1368  debug("sleepTime=%ld", sleepTime);
1369 
1370  if (rem)
1371  {
1372  pRem->tv_sec = 0;
1373  pRem->tv_nsec = 0;
1374  }
1375  return 0;
1376 }
1377

1379 {
1380  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1381  return pcb->ID;
1382 }

1384 static int linux_setitimer(SysFrm *, int which,
1385  const struct itimerspec64 *new_value,
1386  struct itimerspec64 *old_value)
1387 {
1388  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1389  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
1390 
1391  auto pNewValue = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(new_value);
1392  auto pOldValue = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(old_value);
1393  if (pNewValue == nullptr)
1394  return -linux_EFAULT;
1395 
1396  if (pOldValue == nullptr && old_value)
1397  return -linux_EFAULT;
1398 
1399  switch (which)
1400  {
1401  case linux_ITIMER_REAL:
1402  {
1403  fixme("ITIMER_REAL not implemented");
1404  return 0;
1405  }
1406  case linux_ITIMER_VIRTUAL:
1407  {
1408  fixme("ITIMER_VIRTUAL not implemented");
1409  return 0;
1410  }
1411  case linux_ITIMER_PROF:
1412  {
1413  fixme("ITIMER_PROF not implemented");
1414  return 0;
1415  }
1416  default:
1417  return -linux_EINVAL;
1418  }
1419 
1420  return 0;
1421 }

1429 static pid_t linux_fork(SysFrm *sf)
1430 {
1431  TCB *Thread = thisThread;
1432  PCB *Parent = Thread->Parent;
1433 
1434  PCB *NewProcess =
1435  TaskManager->CreateProcess(Parent, Parent->Name,
1436  Parent->Security.ExecutionMode,
1437  true);
1438  if (unlikely(!NewProcess))
1439  {
1440  error("Failed to create process for fork");
1441  return -linux_EAGAIN;
1442  }
1443 
1444  NewProcess->Security.ProcessGroupID = Parent->Security.ProcessGroupID;
1445  NewProcess->Security.SessionID = Parent->Security.SessionID;
1446 
1447  NewProcess->PageTable = Parent->PageTable->Fork();
1448  NewProcess->vma->Table = NewProcess->PageTable;
1449  NewProcess->vma->Fork(Parent->vma);
1450  NewProcess->ProgramBreak->SetTable(NewProcess->PageTable);
1451  NewProcess->FileDescriptors->Fork(Parent->FileDescriptors);
1452  NewProcess->Executable = Parent->Executable;
1453  NewProcess->CWD = Parent->CWD;
1454  NewProcess->FileCreationMask = Parent->FileCreationMask;
1455 
1456  TCB *NewThread =
1457  TaskManager->CreateThread(NewProcess,
1458  0,
1459  nullptr,
1460  nullptr,
1461  std::vector<AuxiliaryVector>(),
1462  Thread->Info.Architecture,
1463  Thread->Info.Compatibility,
1464  true);
1465  if (!NewThread)
1466  {
1467  error("Failed to create thread for fork");
1468  delete NewProcess;
1469  return -linux_EAGAIN;
1470  }
1471  NewThread->Rename(Thread->Name);
1472 
1473  TaskManager->UpdateFrame();
1474 
1475  NewThread->FPU = Thread->FPU;
1476  NewThread->Stack->Fork(Thread->Stack);
1477  NewThread->Info.Architecture = Thread->Info.Architecture;
1478  NewThread->Info.Compatibility = Thread->Info.Compatibility;
1479  NewThread->Security.IsCritical = Thread->Security.IsCritical;
1480  NewThread->Registers = Thread->Registers;
1481 #if defined(a64)
1482  NewThread->Registers.rip = (uintptr_t)__LinuxForkReturn;
1483  /* For sysretq */
1484  NewThread->Registers.rdi = (uintptr_t)NewProcess->PageTable;
1485  NewThread->Registers.rcx = sf->ReturnAddress;
1486  NewThread->Registers.r8 = sf->StackPointer;
1487 #else
1488 #warning "sys_fork not implemented for other platforms"
1489 #endif
1490 
1491 #ifdef a86
1492  NewThread->GSBase = NewThread->ShadowGSBase;
1493  NewThread->ShadowGSBase = Thread->ShadowGSBase;
1494  NewThread->FSBase = Thread->FSBase;
1495 #endif
1496 
1497  debug("ret addr: %#lx, stack: %#lx ip: %#lx", sf->ReturnAddress,
1498  sf->StackPointer, (uintptr_t)__LinuxForkReturn);
1499  debug("Forked thread \"%s\"(%d) to \"%s\"(%d)",
1500  Thread->Name, Thread->ID,
1501  NewThread->Name, NewThread->ID);
1502  NewThread->SetState(Tasking::Ready);
1503 
1504  // Parent->GetContext()->Yield();
1505  return (int)NewProcess->ID;
1506 }
1507 
1508 static pid_t linux_vfork(SysFrm *sf)
1509 {
1510  TCB *Thread = thisThread;
1511  PCB *Parent = Thread->Parent;
1512 
1513  PCB *NewProcess =
1514  TaskManager->CreateProcess(Parent, Parent->Name,
1515  Parent->Security.ExecutionMode,
1516  true);
1517  if (unlikely(!NewProcess))
1518  {
1519  error("Failed to create process for vfork");
1520  return -linux_EAGAIN;
1521  }
1522 
1523  NewProcess->Security.ProcessGroupID = Parent->Security.ProcessGroupID;
1524  NewProcess->Security.SessionID = Parent->Security.SessionID;
1525 
1526  NewProcess->PageTable = Parent->PageTable;
1527  delete NewProcess->vma;
1528  NewProcess->vma = Parent->vma;
1529  delete NewProcess->ProgramBreak;
1530  NewProcess->ProgramBreak = NewProcess->ProgramBreak;
1531  NewProcess->FileDescriptors->Fork(Parent->FileDescriptors);
1532  NewProcess->Executable = Parent->Executable;
1533  NewProcess->CWD = Parent->CWD;
1534  NewProcess->FileCreationMask = Parent->FileCreationMask;
1535 
1536  TCB *NewThread =
1537  TaskManager->CreateThread(NewProcess,
1538  0,
1539  nullptr,
1540  nullptr,
1541  std::vector<AuxiliaryVector>(),
1542  Thread->Info.Architecture,
1543  Thread->Info.Compatibility,
1544  true);
1545  if (!NewThread)
1546  {
1547  error("Failed to create thread for fork");
1548  delete NewProcess;
1549  return -linux_EAGAIN;
1550  }
1551  NewThread->Rename(Thread->Name);
1552 
1553  TaskManager->UpdateFrame();
1554 
1555  NewThread->FPU = Thread->FPU;
1556  delete NewThread->Stack;
1557  NewThread->Stack = Thread->Stack;
1558  NewThread->Info.Architecture = Thread->Info.Architecture;
1559  NewThread->Info.Compatibility = Thread->Info.Compatibility;
1560  NewThread->Security.IsCritical = Thread->Security.IsCritical;
1561  NewThread->Registers = Thread->Registers;
1562 #if defined(a64)
1563  NewThread->Registers.rip = (uintptr_t)__LinuxForkReturn;
1564  /* For sysretq */
1565  NewThread->Registers.rdi = (uintptr_t)NewProcess->PageTable;
1566  NewThread->Registers.rcx = sf->ReturnAddress;
1567  NewThread->Registers.r8 = sf->StackPointer;
1568 #else
1569 #warning "sys_fork not implemented for other platforms"
1570 #endif
1571 
1572 #ifdef a86
1573  NewThread->GSBase = NewThread->ShadowGSBase;
1574  NewThread->ShadowGSBase = Thread->ShadowGSBase;
1575  NewThread->FSBase = Thread->FSBase;
1576 #endif
1577 
1578  debug("ret addr: %#lx, stack: %#lx ip: %#lx", sf->ReturnAddress,
1579  sf->StackPointer, (uintptr_t)__LinuxForkReturn);
1580  debug("Forked thread \"%s\"(%d) to \"%s\"(%d)",
1581  Thread->Name, Thread->ID,
1582  NewThread->Name, NewThread->ID);
1583 
1584  {
1585  CriticalSection cs;
1586  Thread->SetState(Tasking::Frozen);
1587  NewProcess->Linux.vforked = true;
1588  NewProcess->Linux.CallingThread = Thread;
1589  NewThread->SetState(Tasking::Ready);
1590  }
1591  Parent->GetContext()->Yield();
1592  return (int)NewProcess->ID;
1593 }
1594 
1595 __no_sanitize("undefined") static int linux_execve(SysFrm *sf, const char *pathname,
1596  char *const argv[],
1597  char *const envp[])
1598 {
1599  /* FIXME: exec doesn't follow the UNIX standard
1600  The pid, open files, etc. should be preserved */
1601  TCB *tcb = thisThread;
1602  PCB *pcb = tcb->Parent;
1603  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
1604 
1605  auto pPathname = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(pathname, PAGE_SIZE);
1606  auto pArgv = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(argv, 1 /*MAX_ARG*/); /* MAX_ARG is too much? */
1607  auto pEnvp = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(envp, 1 /*MAX_ARG*/);
1608  if (pPathname == nullptr || pArgv == nullptr || pEnvp == nullptr)
1609  return -linux_EFAULT;
1610 
1611  func("%s %#lx %#lx", pPathname, pArgv, pEnvp);
1612 
1613  int argvLen = 0;
1614  for (argvLen = 0; MAX_ARG; argvLen++)
1615  {
1616  if (vma->UserCheck(pArgv[argvLen]) < 0)
1617  break;
1618 
1619  auto arg = pcb->PageTable->Get(pArgv[argvLen]);
1620  if (arg == nullptr)
1621  break;
1622  }
1623 
1624  int envpLen = 0;
1625  for (envpLen = 0; MAX_ARG; envpLen++)
1626  {
1627  if (vma->UserCheck(pEnvp[envpLen]) < 0)
1628  break;
1629 
1630  auto arg = pcb->PageTable->Get(pEnvp[envpLen]);
1631  if (arg == nullptr)
1632  break;
1633  }
1634 
1635  char **safeArgv = (char **)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(argvLen * sizeof(char *)));
1636  char **safeEnvp = (char **)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(envpLen * sizeof(char *)));
1637 
1638  const char *arg;
1639  char *nArg;
1640  for (int i = 0; i < argvLen; i++)
1641  {
1642  arg = pcb->PageTable->Get(pArgv[i]);
1643  assert(arg != nullptr);
1644  size_t len = strlen(arg);
1645  debug("arg[%d]: %s", i, arg);
1646 
1647  nArg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(len));
1648  memcpy((void *)nArg, arg, len);
1649  nArg[len] = '\0';
1650 
1651  safeArgv[i] = nArg;
1652 
1653  if (likely(i < MAX_ARG - 1))
1654  safeArgv[i + 1] = nullptr;
1655  }
1656 
1657  for (int i = 0; i < envpLen; i++)
1658  {
1659  arg = pcb->PageTable->Get(pEnvp[i]);
1660  assert(arg != nullptr);
1661  size_t len = strlen(arg);
1662  debug("env[%d]: %s", i, arg);
1663 
1664  nArg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(len));
1665  memcpy((void *)nArg, arg, len);
1666  nArg[len] = '\0';
1667 
1668  safeEnvp[i] = nArg;
1669 
1670  if (likely(i < MAX_ARG - 1))
1671  safeEnvp[i + 1] = nullptr;
1672  }
1673 
1674  FileNode *file = fs->GetByPath(pPathname, pcb->CWD);
1675 
1676  if (!file)
1677  {
1678  error("File not found");
1679  return -linux_ENOENT;
1680  }
1681 
1682  char shebangMagic[2]{};
1683  file->Read((uint8_t *)shebangMagic, 2, 0);
1684 
1685  if (shebangMagic[0] == '#' && shebangMagic[1] == '!')
1686  {
1687  char *origPath = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(strlen(pPathname) + 1));
1688  memcpy(origPath, pPathname, strlen(pPathname) + 1);
1689 
1690  char *shebang = (char *)pPathname;
1691  size_t shebangLength = 0;
1692  constexpr int shebangLengthMax = 255;
1693  off_t shebangOffset = 2;
1694  while (true)
1695  {
1696  char c;
1697  if (file->Read((uint8_t *)&c, 1, shebangOffset) == 0)
1698  break;
1699  if (c == '\n' || shebangLength == shebangLengthMax)
1700  break;
1701  shebang[shebangLength++] = c;
1702  shebangOffset++;
1703  }
1704  shebang[shebangLength] = '\0';
1705  debug("Shebang: %s", shebang);
1706 
1707  char **cSafeArgv = (char **)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(MAX_ARG));
1708  int i = 0;
1709  for (; safeArgv[i] != nullptr; i++)
1710  {
1711  size_t argLength = strlen(safeArgv[i]);
1712  char *cArg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(argLength));
1713  memcpy((void *)cArg, safeArgv[i], argLength);
1714  cArg[argLength] = '\0';
1715 
1716  cSafeArgv[i] = cArg;
1717  debug("cSafeArgv[%d]: %s", i, cSafeArgv[i]);
1718  }
1719  cSafeArgv[i] = nullptr;
1720 
1721  char *token = strtok(shebang, " ");
1722  i = 0;
1723  while (token != nullptr)
1724  {
1725  size_t len = strlen(token);
1726  char *t_arg = (char *)pcb->vma->RequestPages(TO_PAGES(len));
1727  memcpy((void *)t_arg, token, len);
1728  t_arg[len] = '\0';
1729 
1730  safeArgv[i++] = t_arg;
1731  token = strtok(nullptr, " ");
1732  }
1733 
1734  safeArgv[i++] = origPath;
1735  for (int j = 1; cSafeArgv[j] != nullptr; j++)
1736  {
1737  safeArgv[i++] = cSafeArgv[j];
1738  debug("clone: safeArgv[%d]: %s",
1739  i, safeArgv[i - 1]);
1740  }
1741  safeArgv[i] = nullptr;
1742 
1743  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(linux_execve(sf, safeArgv[0],
1744  (char *const *)safeArgv,
1745  (char *const *)safeEnvp));
1746  }
1747 
1748  if (pcb->Linux.vforked)
1749  {
1750  CriticalSection cs;
1751 
1752  pcb->Linux.CallingThread->SetState(Tasking::Ready);
1753  pcb->Linux.vforked = false;
1754 
1755  pcb->PageTable = KernelPageTable->Fork();
1756  pcb->vma = new Memory::VirtualMemoryArea(pcb->PageTable);
1757  pcb->ProgramBreak = new Memory::ProgramBreak(pcb->PageTable, pcb->vma);
1758  // tcb->Stack = new Memory::StackGuard(true, pcb->vma);
1759  }
1760 
1761  int ret = Execute::Spawn((char *)pPathname,
1762  (const char **)safeArgv,
1763  (const char **)safeEnvp,
1764  pcb, true,
1765  pcb->Info.Compatibility);
1766 
1767  if (ret < 0)
1768  {
1769  error("Failed to spawn");
1770  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(ret);
1771  }
1772 
1773  const char *baseName;
1774  cwk_path_get_basename(pPathname, &baseName, nullptr);
1775 
1776  pcb->Rename(baseName);
1777  pcb->SetWorkingDirectory(file->Parent);
1778  pcb->SetExe(pPathname);
1779 
1780  Tasking::Task *ctx = pcb->GetContext();
1781  // ctx->Sleep(1000);
1782  // pcb->SetState(Tasking::Zombie);
1783  // pcb->SetExitCode(0); /* FIXME: get process exit code */
1784  while (true)
1785  ctx->Yield();
1786  __builtin_unreachable();
1787 }
1788 
1789 static __noreturn void linux_exit(SysFrm *, int status)
1790 {
1791  TCB *t = thisThread;
1792  {
1793  CriticalSection cs;
1794  trace("Userspace thread %s(%d) exited with code %d (%#x)",
1795  t->Name,
1796  t->ID, status,
1797  status < 0 ? -status : status);
1798 
1799  t->SetState(Tasking::Zombie);
1800  t->SetExitCode(status);
1801  if (t->Parent->Linux.vforked)
1802  t->Parent->Linux.CallingThread->SetState(Tasking::Ready);
1803  }
1804  while (true)
1805  t->GetContext()->Yield();
1806  __builtin_unreachable();
1807 }
1808 
1809 static pid_t linux_wait4(SysFrm *, pid_t pid, int *wstatus,
1810  int options, struct rusage *rusage)
1811 {
1812  static_assert(sizeof(struct rusage) < PAGE_SIZE);
1813  /* FIXME: this function is very poorly implemented, the way
1814  it handles the zombie & coredump processes is very
1815  inefficient and should be rewritten */
1816 
1817  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
1818  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
1819 
1820  if (pid == -1)
1821  {
1822  if (pcb->Children.empty())
1823  {
1824  debug("No children");
1825  return -linux_ECHILD;
1826  }
1827 
1828  std::vector<PCB *> wChilds;
1829  for (auto child : pcb->Children)
1830  {
1831  if (child->State == Tasking::Zombie)
1832  {
1833  if (wstatus != nullptr)
1834  {
1835  int *pWstatus = pcb->PageTable->Get(wstatus);
1836  *pWstatus = 0;
1837 
1838  bool ProcessExited = true;
1839  int ExitStatus = child->ExitCode.load();
1840 
1841  debug("Process returned %d", ExitStatus);
1842 
1843  if (ProcessExited)
1844  *pWstatus |= ExitStatus << 8;
1845  }
1846 
1847  if (rusage != nullptr)
1848  {
1849  size_t kTime = child->Info.KernelTime;
1850  size_t uTime = child->Info.UserTime;
1851  size_t _maxrss = child->GetSize();
1852 
1853  struct rusage *pRusage = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(rusage);
1854  if (pRusage == nullptr)
1855  return -linux_EFAULT;
1856 
1857  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1858  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1859 
1860  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1861  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1862 
1863  pRusage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
1864  }
1865 
1866  child->SetState(Tasking::Terminated);
1867  return child->ID;
1868  }
1869 
1870  if (child->State == Tasking::CoreDump)
1871  {
1872  if (wstatus != nullptr)
1873  {
1874  int *pWstatus = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(wstatus);
1875  if (pWstatus == nullptr)
1876  return -linux_EFAULT;
1877  *pWstatus = 0;
1878 
1879  bool ProcessExited = true;
1880  int ExitStatus = child->ExitCode.load();
1881  bool ProcessSignaled = true;
1882  bool CoreDumped = true;
1883  int TermSignal = child->Signals.GetLastSignal();
1884  TermSignal = ConvertSignalToLinux((Signals)TermSignal);
1885  assert(TermSignal != SIG_NULL);
1886 
1887  debug("Process returned %d", ExitStatus);
1888 
1889  if (ProcessExited)
1890  *pWstatus |= ExitStatus << 8;
1891 
1892  if (ProcessSignaled)
1893  *pWstatus |= TermSignal;
1894 
1895  if (CoreDumped)
1896  *pWstatus |= 0x80;
1897  }
1898 
1899  if (rusage != nullptr)
1900  {
1901  size_t kTime = child->Info.KernelTime;
1902  size_t uTime = child->Info.UserTime;
1903  size_t _maxrss = child->GetSize();
1904 
1905  struct rusage *pRusage = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(rusage);
1906  if (pRusage == nullptr)
1907  return -linux_EFAULT;
1908 
1909  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1910  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1911 
1912  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
1913  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
1914 
1915  pRusage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
1916  }
1917 
1918  child->SetState(Tasking::Terminated);
1919  return child->ID;
1920  }
1921 
1922  if (child->State != Tasking::Terminated)
1923  wChilds.push_back(child);
1924  }
1925 
1926  if (wChilds.empty())
1927  {
1928  debug("No children");
1929  return -linux_ECHILD;
1930  }
1931 
1932  fixme("Waiting for %d children", wChilds.size());
1933  pid = wChilds.front()->ID;
1934  }
1935 
1936  if (pid == 0)
1937  {
1938  fixme("Waiting for any child process whose process group ID is equal to that of the calling process");
1939  return -linux_ENOSYS;
1940  }
1941 
1942  if (pid < -1)
1943  {
1944  fixme("Waiting for any child process whose process group ID is equal to the absolute value of pid");
1945  return -linux_ENOSYS;
1946  }
1947 
1948  /* Wait for a child process, or any process? */
1949  PCB *tPcb = pcb->GetContext()->GetProcessByID(pid);
1950  if (!tPcb)
1951  {
1952  warn("Invalid PID %d", pid);
1953  return -linux_ECHILD;
1954  }
1955 
1956  if (options)
1957  {
1958 #define WCONTINUED 1
1959 #define WNOHANG 2
1960 #define WUNTRACED 4
1961 #define WEXITED 8
1962 #define WNOWAIT 16
1963 #define WSTOPPED 32
1964  fixme("options=%#x", options);
1965  }
1966 
1967 #ifdef DEBUG
1968  foreach (auto child in pcb->Children)
1969  debug("Child: %s(%d)", child->Name, child->ID);
1970 #endif
1971 
1972  debug("Waiting for %d(%#lx) state %d", pid, tPcb, tPcb->State);
1973  while (tPcb->State != Tasking::Zombie &&
1974  tPcb->State != Tasking::CoreDump &&
1975  tPcb->State != Tasking::Terminated)
1976  pcb->GetContext()->Yield();
1977  debug("Waited for %d(%#lx) state %d", pid, tPcb, tPcb->State);
1978 
1979  if (wstatus != nullptr)
1980  {
1981  int *pWstatus = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(wstatus);
1982  if (pWstatus == nullptr)
1983  return -linux_EFAULT;
1984  *pWstatus = 0;
1985 
1986  bool ProcessExited = true;
1987  int ExitStatus = tPcb->ExitCode.load();
1988  bool ProcessSignaled = false;
1989  bool CoreDumped = false;
1990  bool ProcessStopped = false;
1991  bool ProcessContinued = false;
1992  int TermSignal = 0;
1993 
1994  debug("Process returned %d", ExitStatus);
1995 
1996  if (ProcessExited)
1997  *pWstatus |= ExitStatus << 8;
1998 
1999  if (ProcessSignaled)
2000  *pWstatus |= TermSignal;
2001 
2002  if (CoreDumped)
2003  *pWstatus |= 0x80;
2004 
2005  /* FIXME: Untested */
2006 
2007  if (ProcessStopped)
2008  *pWstatus |= 0x7F;
2009 
2010  if (ProcessContinued)
2011  *pWstatus = 0xFFFF;
2012 
2013  debug("wstatus=%#x", *pWstatus);
2014  }
2015 
2016  if (rusage != nullptr)
2017  {
2018  size_t kTime = tPcb->Info.KernelTime;
2019  size_t uTime = tPcb->Info.UserTime;
2020  size_t _maxrss = tPcb->GetSize();
2021 
2022  struct rusage *pRusage = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(rusage);
2023  if (pRusage == nullptr)
2024  return -linux_EFAULT;
2025 
2026  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2027  pRusage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2028 
2029  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2030  pRusage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2031 
2032  pRusage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
2033  /* TODO: The rest of the fields */
2034  }
2035 
2036  return pid;
2037 }
2038 
2039 static int linux_kill(SysFrm *, pid_t pid, int sig)
2040 {
2041  PCB *pcb = thisProcess->GetContext()->GetProcessByID(pid);
2042  if (!pcb)
2043  return -linux_ESRCH;
2044 
2045  /* TODO: Check permissions */
2046 
2047  if (sig == 0)
2048  return 0;
2049 
2050  if (pid == 0)
2051  {
2052  bool found = false;
2053  Signals nSig = ConvertSignalToNative(sig);
2054  assert(nSig != SIG_NULL);
2055  foreach (auto proc in pcb->GetContext()->GetProcessList())
2056  {
2057  if (proc->Security.ProcessGroupID == thisProcess->Security.ProcessGroupID)
2058  {
2059  debug("Sending signal %s to %s(%d)", lSigStr[sig], proc->Name, proc->ID);
2060  proc->SendSignal(nSig);
2061  found = true;
2062  }
2063  }
2064  if (!found)
2065  return -linux_ESRCH;
2066  return 0;
2067  }
2068 
2069  if (pid == -1)
2070  {
2071  fixme("Sending signal %d to all processes except init", sig);
2072  return -linux_ENOSYS;
2073  }
2074 
2075  if (pid < -1)
2076  {
2077  fixme("Sending signal %d to process group %d", sig, pid);
2078  return -linux_ENOSYS;
2079  }
2080 
2081  Signals nSig = ConvertSignalToNative(sig);
2082  assert(nSig != SIG_NULL);
2083  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(pcb->SendSignal(nSig));
2084 }
2085 
2086 static int linux_uname(SysFrm *, struct utsname *buf)
2087 {
2088  assert(sizeof(struct utsname) < PAGE_SIZE);
2089 
2090  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2091  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2092 
2093  auto pBuf = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(buf);
2094  if (pBuf == nullptr)
2095  return -linux_EFAULT;
2096 
2097  struct utsname uname =
2098  {
2099  /* TODO: This shouldn't be hardcoded */
2100  .sysname = KERNEL_NAME,
2101  .nodename = "fennix",
2102  .release = KERNEL_VERSION,
2103  .version = KERNEL_VERSION,
2104 #if defined(a64)
2105  .machine = "x86_64",
2106 #elif defined(a32)
2107  .machine = "i386",
2108 #elif defined(aa64)
2109  .machine = "arm64",
2110 #elif defined(aa32)
2111  .machine = "arm",
2112 #endif
2113  };
2114 
2115  FileNode *rn = fs->GetByPath("/etc/cross/linux", pcb->Info.RootNode);
2116  if (rn)
2117  {
2118  struct kstat st
2119  {
2120  };
2121  rn->Stat(&st);
2122 
2123  char *sh = new char[st.Size];
2124  rn->Read(sh, st.Size, 0);
2125 
2126  ini_t *ini = ini_load(sh, NULL);
2127  int section = ini_find_section(ini, "uname", NULL);
2128  int sysIdx = ini_find_property(ini, section, "sysname", NULL);
2129  int nodIdx = ini_find_property(ini, section, "nodename", NULL);
2130  int relIdx = ini_find_property(ini, section, "release", NULL);
2131  int verIdx = ini_find_property(ini, section, "version", NULL);
2132  int macIdx = ini_find_property(ini, section, "machine", NULL);
2133  const char *uSys = ini_property_value(ini, section, sysIdx);
2134  const char *uNod = ini_property_value(ini, section, nodIdx);
2135  const char *uRel = ini_property_value(ini, section, relIdx);
2136  const char *uVer = ini_property_value(ini, section, verIdx);
2137  const char *uMac = ini_property_value(ini, section, macIdx);
2138  debug("sysname=%s", uSys);
2139  debug("nodename=%s", uNod);
2140  debug("release=%s", uRel);
2141  debug("version=%s", uVer);
2142  debug("machine=%s", uMac);
2143 
2144  if (uSys && strcmp(uSys, "auto") != 0)
2145  strncpy(uname.sysname, uSys, sizeof(uname.sysname));
2146  if (uNod && strcmp(uNod, "auto") != 0)
2147  strncpy(uname.nodename, uNod, sizeof(uname.nodename));
2148  if (uRel && strcmp(uRel, "auto") != 0)
2149  strncpy(uname.release, uRel, sizeof(uname.release));
2150  if (uVer && strcmp(uVer, "auto") != 0)
2151  strncpy(uname.version, uVer, sizeof(uname.version));
2152  if (uMac && strcmp(uMac, "auto") != 0)
2153  strncpy(uname.machine, uMac, sizeof(uname.machine));
2154  ini_destroy(ini);
2155 
2156  delete[] sh;
2157  }
2158  else
2159  warn("Couldn't open /etc/cross/linux");
2160 
2161  memcpy(pBuf, &uname, sizeof(struct utsname));
2162  return 0;
2163 }

2165 static int linux_fcntl(SysFrm *, int fd, int cmd, void *arg)
2166 {
2167  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2168  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
2169 
2170  switch (cmd)
2171  {
2172  case linux_F_DUPFD:
2173  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->usr_dup2(fd, s_cst(int, (uintptr_t)arg)));
2174  case linux_F_GETFD:
2175  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->GetFlags(fd));
2176  case linux_F_SETFD:
2177  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->SetFlags(fd, s_cst(int, (uintptr_t)arg)));
2178  case linux_F_GETFL:
2179  {
2180  fixme("F_GETFL is stub?");
2181  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(fdt->GetFlags(fd));
2182  }
2183  case linux_F_SETFL:
2184  {
2185  fixme("F_SETFL is stub?");
2186  int flags = s_cst(int, (uintptr_t)arg);
2187  if (flags & O_APPEND)
2188  fdt->SetFlags(fd, fdt->GetFlags(fd) | O_APPEND);
2189  else
2190  fdt->SetFlags(fd, fdt->GetFlags(fd) & ~O_APPEND);
2191  return 0;
2192  }
2193  case linux_F_DUPFD_CLOEXEC:
2194  {
2195  int ret = fdt->usr_dup2(fd, s_cst(int, (uintptr_t)arg));
2196  if (ret < 0)
2197  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(ret);
2198 
2199  auto it = fdt->FileMap.find(fd);
2200  if (it == fdt->FileMap.end())
2201  ReturnLogError(-linux_EBADF, "Invalid fd %d", fd);
2202 
2203  it->second.Flags |= linux_FD_CLOEXEC;
2204  return ret;
2205  }
2206  case linux_F_SETOWN:
2207  case linux_F_GETOWN:
2208  case linux_F_SETSIG:
2209  case linux_F_GETSIG:
2210  case linux_F_GETLK:
2211  case linux_F_SETLK:
2212  case linux_F_SETLKW:
2213  case linux_F_SETOWN_EX:
2214  case linux_F_GETOWN_EX:
2215  case linux_F_GETOWNER_UIDS:
2216  case linux_F_OFD_GETLK:
2217  case linux_F_OFD_SETLK:
2218  case linux_F_OFD_SETLKW:
2219  {
2220  fixme("cmd %d not implemented", cmd);
2221  return -linux_ENOSYS;
2222  }
2223  default:
2224  {
2225  debug("Invalid cmd %#x", cmd);
2226  return -linux_EINVAL;
2227  }
2228  }
2229 }

2240  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;

2255  pBuf[cwd.length()] = '\0';
2256  debug("cwd: \"%s\" with %ld bytes", cwd.c_str(), cwd.length());
2257  return cwd.length();

2310 static ssize_t linux_readlink(SysFrm *, const char *pathname,
2311  char *buf, size_t bufsiz)
2312 {
2313  if (!pathname || !buf)
2314  return -linux_EINVAL;
2315 
2316  if (bufsiz > PAGE_SIZE)
2317  {
2318  warn("bufsiz is too large: %ld", bufsiz);
2319  return -linux_EINVAL;
2320  }
2321 
2322  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2323  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2324 
2325  const char *pPath = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(pathname);
2326  char *pBuf = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(buf);
2327  if (pPath == nullptr || pBuf == nullptr)
2328  return -linux_EFAULT;
2329 
2330  func("%s %#lx %ld", pPath, buf, bufsiz);
2331  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
2332  int fd = fdt->usr_open(pPath, O_RDONLY, 0);
2333  if (fd < 0)
2334  return -linux_ENOENT;
2335 
2336  auto it = fdt->FileMap.find(fd);
2337  if (it == fdt->FileMap.end())
2338  ReturnLogError(-linux_EBADF, "Invalid fd %d", fd);
2339 
2340  vfs::FileDescriptorTable::Fildes &fildes = it->second;
2341  FileNode *node = fildes.Node;
2342  fdt->usr_close(fd);
2343 
2344  if (!node->IsSymbolicLink())
2345  return -linux_EINVAL;
2346 
2347  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(node->ReadLink(pBuf, bufsiz));
2348 }

2359 static int linux_getrusage(SysFrm *, int who, struct rusage *usage)
2360 {
2361  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2362  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2363 
2364  auto pUsage = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(usage);
2365  if (pUsage == nullptr)
2366  return -linux_EFAULT;
2367 
2368  switch (who)
2369  {
2370  case linux_RUSAGE_SELF:
2371  {
2372  size_t kTime = pcb->Info.KernelTime;
2373  size_t uTime = pcb->Info.UserTime;
2374  size_t _maxrss = pcb->GetSize();
2375 
2376  pUsage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2377  pUsage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2378 
2379  pUsage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2380  pUsage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2381 
2382  pUsage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
2383  break;
2384  }
2385  case linux_RUSAGE_CHILDREN:
2386  {
2387  size_t kTime = 0;
2388  size_t uTime = 0;
2389  size_t _maxrss = 0;
2390 
2391  foreach (auto child in pcb->Children)
2392  {
2393  kTime += child->Info.KernelTime;
2394  uTime += child->Info.UserTime;
2395  _maxrss += child->GetSize();
2396  }
2397 
2398  pUsage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2399  pUsage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2400 
2401  pUsage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2402  pUsage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2403 
2404  pUsage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
2405  break;
2406  }
2407  case linux_RUSAGE_THREAD:
2408  {
2409  TCB *tcb = thisThread;
2410 
2411  size_t kTime = tcb->Info.KernelTime;
2412  size_t uTime = tcb->Info.UserTime;
2413  size_t _maxrss = tcb->GetSize();
2414 
2415  pUsage->ru_utime.tv_sec = uTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2416  pUsage->ru_utime.tv_usec = uTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2417 
2418  pUsage->ru_stime.tv_sec = kTime / 1000000000000000; /* Seconds */
2419  pUsage->ru_stime.tv_usec = kTime / 1000000000; /* Microseconds */
2420 
2421  pUsage->ru_maxrss = _maxrss;
2422  break;
2423  }
2424  default:
2425  return -linux_EINVAL;
2426  }
2427 
2428  return 0;
2429 }

2492 static int linux_arch_prctl(SysFrm *, int code, unsigned long addr)
2493 {
2494  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2495  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2496 
2497  if (vma->UserCheck(addr) < 0)
2498  return -linux_EFAULT;
2499 
2500  switch (code)
2501  {
2502  case linux_ARCH_SET_GS:
2503  {
2504 #if defined(a64)
2505  CPU::x64::wrmsr(CPU::x64::MSRID::MSR_GS_BASE, addr);
2506 #elif defined(a32)
2507  CPU::x32::wrmsr(CPU::x32::MSRID::MSR_GS_BASE, addr);
2508 #endif
2509  return 0;
2510  }
2511  case linux_ARCH_SET_FS:
2512  {
2513 #if defined(a64)
2514  CPU::x64::wrmsr(CPU::x64::MSRID::MSR_FS_BASE, addr);
2515 #elif defined(a32)
2516  CPU::x32::wrmsr(CPU::x32::MSRID::MSR_FS_BASE, addr);
2517 #endif
2518  return 0;
2519  }
2520  case linux_ARCH_GET_FS:
2521  {
2522 #if defined(a64)
2523  *r_cst(uint64_t *, addr) =
2524  CPU::x64::rdmsr(CPU::x64::MSRID::MSR_FS_BASE);
2525 #elif defined(a32)
2526  *r_cst(uint64_t *, addr) =
2527  CPU::x32::rdmsr(CPU::x32::MSRID::MSR_FS_BASE);
2528 #endif
2529  return 0;
2530  }
2531  case linux_ARCH_GET_GS:
2532  {
2533 #if defined(a64)
2534  *r_cst(uint64_t *, addr) =
2535  CPU::x64::rdmsr(CPU::x64::MSRID::MSR_GS_BASE);
2536 #elif defined(a32)
2537  *r_cst(uint64_t *, addr) =
2538  CPU::x32::rdmsr(CPU::x32::MSRID::MSR_GS_BASE);
2539 #endif
2540  return 0;
2541  }
2542  case linux_ARCH_GET_CPUID:
2543  case linux_ARCH_SET_CPUID:
2544  case linux_ARCH_GET_XCOMP_SUPP:
2545  case linux_ARCH_GET_XCOMP_PERM:
2546  case linux_ARCH_REQ_XCOMP_PERM:
2547  case linux_ARCH_GET_XCOMP_GUEST_PERM:
2548  case linux_ARCH_REQ_XCOMP_GUEST_PERM:
2549  case linux_ARCH_XCOMP_TILECFG:
2550  case linux_ARCH_XCOMP_TILEDATA:
2551  case linux_ARCH_MAP_VDSO_X32:
2552  case linux_ARCH_MAP_VDSO_32:
2553  case linux_ARCH_MAP_VDSO_64:
2554  case linux_ARCH_GET_UNTAG_MASK:
2555  case linux_ARCH_ENABLE_TAGGED_ADDR:
2556  case linux_ARCH_GET_MAX_TAG_BITS:
2557  case linux_ARCH_FORCE_TAGGED_SVA:
2558  {
2559  fixme("Code %#lx not implemented", code);
2560  return -linux_ENOSYS;
2561  }
2562  default:
2563  {
2564  debug("Invalid code %#lx", code);
2565  return -linux_EINVAL;
2566  }
2567  }
2568 }

2570 static int linux_reboot(SysFrm *, int magic, int magic2, int cmd, void *arg)
2571 {
2572  if (magic != linux_LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC1 ||
2573  (magic2 != linux_LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2 &&
2574  magic2 != linux_LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2A &&
2575  magic2 != linux_LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2B &&
2576  magic2 != linux_LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2C))
2577  {
2578  warn("Invalid magic %#x %#x", magic, magic2);
2579  return -linux_EINVAL;
2580  }
2581 
2582  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2583  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2584 
2585  debug("cmd=%#x arg=%#lx", cmd, arg);
2586  switch ((unsigned int)cmd)
2587  {
2588  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_RESTART:
2589  {
2590  KPrint("Restarting system.");
2591 
2592  Tasking::Task *ctx = pcb->GetContext();
2593  ctx->CreateThread(ctx->GetKernelProcess(),
2594  Tasking::IP(KST_Reboot))
2595  ->Rename("Restart");
2596  return 0;
2597  }
2598  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_HALT:
2599  {
2600  KPrint("System halted.");
2601 
2602  pcb->GetContext()->Panic();
2603  CPU::Stop();
2604  }
2605  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_POWER_OFF:
2606  {
2607  KPrint("Power down.");
2608 
2609  Tasking::Task *ctx = pcb->GetContext();
2610  ctx->CreateThread(ctx->GetKernelProcess(),
2611  Tasking::IP(KST_Shutdown))
2612  ->Rename("Shutdown");
2613  return 0;
2614  }
2615  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_RESTART2:
2616  {
2617  void *pArg = vma->__UserCheckAndGetAddress(arg, sizeof(void *));
2618  if (pArg == nullptr)
2619  return -linux_EFAULT;
2620 
2621  KPrint("Restarting system with command '%s'",
2622  (const char *)pArg);
2623 
2624  Tasking::Task *ctx = pcb->GetContext();
2625  ctx->CreateThread(ctx->GetKernelProcess(),
2626  Tasking::IP(KST_Reboot))
2627  ->Rename("Restart");
2628  break;
2629  }
2630  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_CAD_ON:
2631  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_CAD_OFF:
2632  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_SW_SUSPEND:
2633  case linux_LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_KEXEC:
2634  {
2635  fixme("cmd %#x not implemented", cmd);
2636  return -linux_ENOSYS;
2637  }
2638  default:
2639  {
2640  debug("Invalid cmd %#x", cmd);
2641  return -linux_EINVAL;
2642  }
2643  }
2644  return 0;
2645 }
2646 
2647 static int linux_sigaction(SysFrm *, int signum, const k_sigaction *act,
2648  k_sigaction *oldact, size_t sigsetsize)
2649 {
2650  if (signum < 1 || signum > linux_SIGRTMAX ||
2651  signum == linux_SIGKILL || signum == linux_SIGSTOP)
2652  {
2653  debug("Invalid signal %d", signum);
2654  return -linux_EINVAL;
2655  }
2656 
2657  if (sigsetsize != sizeof(sigset_t))
2658  {
2659  warn("Unsupported sigsetsize %d!", sigsetsize);
2660  return -linux_EINVAL;
2661  }
2662 
2663  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2664  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2665 
2666  debug("signum=%d act=%#lx oldact=%#lx", signum, act, oldact);
2667 
2668  if (vma->UserCheck(act) < 0 && act != nullptr)
2669  return -linux_EFAULT;
2670  if (vma->UserCheck(oldact) < 0 && oldact != nullptr)
2671  return -linux_EFAULT;
2672 
2673  auto pAct = pcb->PageTable->Get(act);
2674  auto pOldact = pcb->PageTable->Get(oldact);
2675  int ret = 0;
2676 
2677  if (pOldact)
2678  {
2679  Signals nSig = ConvertSignalToNative(signum);
2680  assert(nSig != SIG_NULL);
2681 
2682  SignalAction nSA{};
2683  SetSigActToNative(pOldact, &nSA);
2684  ret = pcb->Signals.GetAction(nSig, &nSA);
2685  SetSigActToLinux(&nSA, pOldact);
2686  }
2687 
2688  if (unlikely(ret < 0))
2689  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(ret);
2690 
2691  if (pAct)
2692  {
2693  if (pAct->flags & linux_SA_IMMUTABLE)
2694  {
2695  warn("Immutable signal %d", signum);
2696  return -linux_EINVAL;
2697  }
2698 
2699  Signals nSig = ConvertSignalToNative(signum);
2700  assert(nSig != SIG_NULL);
2701 
2702  SignalAction nSA{};
2703  SetSigActToNative(pAct, &nSA);
2704  ret = pcb->Signals.SetAction(nSig, &nSA);
2705  SetSigActToLinux(&nSA, (k_sigaction *)pAct);
2706  }
2707 
2708  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(ret);
2709 }
2710 
2711 static int linux_sigprocmask(SysFrm *, int how, const sigset_t *set,
2712  sigset_t *oldset, size_t sigsetsize)
2713 {
2714  static_assert(sizeof(sigset_t) < PAGE_SIZE);
2715 
2716  if (sigsetsize != sizeof(sigset_t))
2717  {
2718  warn("Unsupported sigsetsize %d!", sigsetsize);
2719  return -linux_EINVAL;
2720  }
2721 
2722  TCB *tcb = thisThread;
2723  PCB *pcb = tcb->Parent;
2724  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2725 
2726  if (vma->UserCheck(set) < 0 && set != nullptr)
2727  return -linux_EFAULT;
2728  if (vma->UserCheck(oldset) < 0 && oldset != nullptr)
2729  return -linux_EFAULT;
2730 
2731  const sigset_t *pSet = (const sigset_t *)pcb->PageTable->Get((void *)set);
2732  sigset_t *pOldset = (sigset_t *)pcb->PageTable->Get(oldset);
2733 
2734  debug("how=%#x set=%#lx oldset=%#lx",
2735  how, pSet ? *pSet : 0, pOldset ? *pOldset : 0);
2736 
2737  if (pOldset)
2738  {
2739  *pOldset = tcb->Signals.GetMask();
2740  *pOldset = ConvertMaskToLinux(*pOldset);
2741  }
2742 
2743  if (!pSet)
2744  return 0;
2745 
2746  sigset_t nativeSet = ConvertMaskToNative(*pSet);
2747  switch (how)
2748  {
2749  case SIG_BLOCK:
2750  tcb->Signals.Block(nativeSet);
2751  break;
2752  case SIG_UNBLOCK:
2753  tcb->Signals.Unblock(nativeSet);
2754  break;
2755  case SIG_SETMASK:
2756  tcb->Signals.SetMask(nativeSet);
2757  break;
2758  default:
2759  warn("Invalid how %#x", how);
2760  return -linux_EINVAL;
2761  }
2762  return 0;
2763 }

2766 {
2767  thisProcess->Signals.RestoreHandleSignal(sf, thisThread);
2768 }

2786 static int linux_sched_setaffinity(SysFrm *, pid_t pid, size_t cpusetsize, const cpu_set_t *mask)
2787 {
2788  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2789  TCB *tcb;
2790  if (pid == 0)
2791  tcb = thisThread;
2792  else
2793  tcb = pcb->GetThread(pid);
2794 
2795  if (!tcb)
2796  return -linux_ESRCH;
2797 
2798  if (cpusetsize < sizeof(cpu_set_t))
2799  return -linux_EINVAL;
2800 
2801  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2802  auto pMask = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(mask);
2803  if (pMask == nullptr && mask != nullptr)
2804  return -linux_EFAULT;
2805 
2806  for (size_t i = 0; i < MAX_CPU && i < CPU_SETSIZE; ++i)
2807  {
2808  if (CPU_ISSET(i, pMask))
2809  tcb->Info.Affinity[i] = true;
2810  else
2811  tcb->Info.Affinity[i] = false;
2812  }
2813 
2814 #ifdef DEBUG
2815  for (size_t i = 0; i < MAX_CPU && i < CPU_SETSIZE; ++i)
2816  {
2817  bool isset = CPU_ISSET(i, pMask);
2818  bool affinity = tcb->Info.Affinity[i];
2819  if (isset != affinity)
2820  {
2821  fixme("sched_setaffinity check failed %d != %d (cpu %d)",
2822  isset, affinity, i);
2823  assert(isset == affinity);
2824  }
2825  }
2826 #endif
2827  return 0;
2828 }
2829 
2830 static int linux_sched_getaffinity(SysFrm *, pid_t pid, size_t cpusetsize, cpu_set_t *mask)
2831 {
2832  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2833  TCB *tcb;
2834  if (pid == 0)
2835  tcb = thisThread;
2836  else
2837  tcb = pcb->GetThread(pid);
2838 
2839  if (!tcb)
2840  return -linux_ESRCH;
2841 
2842  if (cpusetsize < sizeof(cpu_set_t))
2843  return -linux_EINVAL;
2844 
2845  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2846  auto pMask = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(mask);
2847  if (pMask == nullptr && mask != nullptr)
2848  return -linux_EFAULT;
2849 
2850  CPU_ZERO(pMask);
2851 
2852  for (size_t i = 0; i < MAX_CPU && i < CPU_SETSIZE; ++i)
2853  {
2854  if (tcb->Info.Affinity[i])
2855  CPU_SET(i, pMask);
2856  }
2857 
2858  return 0;
2859 }

2872 __no_sanitize("undefined") static ssize_t linux_getdents64(SysFrm *,
2873  int fd, struct linux_dirent64 *dirp, size_t count)
2874 {
2875  if (unlikely(count < sizeof(struct linux_dirent64)))
2876  {
2877  debug("Invalid count %d", count);
2878  return -linux_EINVAL;
2879  }
2880 
2881  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
2882  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
2883  auto it = fdt->FileMap.find(fd);
2884  if (it == fdt->FileMap.end())
2885  {
2886  debug("Invalid fd %d", fd);
2887  return -linux_EBADF;
2888  }
2889 
2890  vfs::FileDescriptorTable::Fildes &fildes = it->second;
2891  if (!fildes.Node->IsDirectory())
2892  {
2893  debug("Not a directory");
2894  return -ENOTDIR;
2895  }
2896 
2897  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
2898  auto pDirp = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(dirp);
2899  if (pDirp == nullptr)
2900  return -linux_EFAULT;
2901 
2902  /* Sanity checks */
2903  static_assert(sizeof(kdirent) == sizeof(linux_dirent64));
2904  static_assert(offsetof(kdirent, d_ino) == offsetof(linux_dirent64, d_ino));
2905  static_assert(offsetof(kdirent, d_off) == offsetof(linux_dirent64, d_off));
2906  static_assert(offsetof(kdirent, d_reclen) == offsetof(linux_dirent64, d_reclen));
2907  static_assert(offsetof(kdirent, d_type) == offsetof(linux_dirent64, d_type));
2908  static_assert(offsetof(kdirent, d_name) == offsetof(linux_dirent64, d_name));
2909 
2910  /* The structs are the same, no need for conversion. */
2911  ssize_t ret = fildes.Node->ReadDir((struct kdirent *)pDirp, count, fildes.Offset,
2912  count / sizeof(kdirent));
2913 
2914  if (ret > 0)
2915  fildes.Offset += ret;
2916 
2917 #ifdef DEBUG
2918  if (ret > 0)
2919  {
2920  for (size_t bpos = 0; bpos < ret;)
2921  {
2922  linux_dirent64 *d = (struct linux_dirent64 *)((char *)pDirp + bpos);
2923  debug("%ld: d_ino:%d d_off:%d d_reclen:%d d_type:%d(%s) d_name:\"%s\"",
2924  bpos, d->d_ino, d->d_off, d->d_reclen, d->d_type,
2925  (d->d_type == DT_REG) ? "REG"
2926  : (d->d_type == DT_DIR) ? "DIR"
2927  : (d->d_type == DT_FIFO) ? "FIFO"
2928  : (d->d_type == DT_SOCK) ? "SOCK"
2929  : (d->d_type == DT_LNK) ? "LNK"
2930  : (d->d_type == DT_BLK) ? "BLK"
2931  : (d->d_type == DT_CHR) ? "CHR"
2932  : "???",
2933  d->d_name);
2934 
2935  bpos += (d->d_reclen == 0) ? 1 : d->d_reclen;
2936  }
2937  }
2938 #endif
2939  return ret;
2940 }

2942 static int linux_clock_gettime(SysFrm *, clockid_t clockid, struct timespec *tp)
2943 {

2997 static int linux_clock_nanosleep(SysFrm *, clockid_t clockid, int flags,
2998  const struct timespec *request,
2999  struct timespec *remain)
3000 {
3001  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
3002  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
3003 
3004  const timespec *pRequest = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(request);
3005  timespec *pRemain = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(remain);
3006  if (pRequest == nullptr)
3007  return -linux_EFAULT;
3008 
3009  UNUSED(pRemain);
3010  UNUSED(flags);
3011 
3012  switch (clockid)
3013  {
3014  case linux_CLOCK_REALTIME:
3015  case linux_CLOCK_MONOTONIC:
3016  {
3017  uint64_t time = TimeManager->GetCounter();
3018  uint64_t rqTime = pRequest->tv_sec * Time::ConvertUnit(Time::Seconds) +
3019  pRequest->tv_nsec * Time::ConvertUnit(Time::Nanoseconds);
3020 
3021  debug("Sleeping for %ld", rqTime - time);
3022  if (rqTime > time)
3023  pcb->GetContext()->Sleep(rqTime - time);
3024  break;
3025  }
3026  case linux_CLOCK_PROCESS_CPUTIME_ID:
3027  case linux_CLOCK_THREAD_CPUTIME_ID:
3028  case linux_CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW:
3029  case linux_CLOCK_REALTIME_COARSE:
3030  case linux_CLOCK_MONOTONIC_COARSE:
3031  case linux_CLOCK_BOOTTIME:
3032  case linux_CLOCK_REALTIME_ALARM:
3033  case linux_CLOCK_BOOTTIME_ALARM:
3034  case linux_CLOCK_SGI_CYCLE:
3035  case linux_CLOCK_TAI:
3036  {
3037  fixme("clockid %d is stub", clockid);
3038  return -linux_ENOSYS;
3039  }
3040  default:
3041  {
3042  warn("Invalid clockid %#lx", clockid);
3043  return -linux_EINVAL;
3044  }
3045  }
3046  return 0;

3082 static int linux_openat(SysFrm *, int dirfd, const char *pathname, int flags, mode_t mode)
3083 {

3087

3089  if (pPathname == nullptr)
3090  return -linux_EFAULT;

3093  dirfd, pPathname, flags, mode);
3094

3096  {

3098  if (!absoluteNode)

3102  strcpy((char *)absPath, absoluteNode->Path.c_str());
3103  int ret = fdt->usr_open(absPath, flags, mode);
3104  delete[] absPath;
3105  return ConvertErrnoToLinux(ret);
3106  }
3107 
3108  if (!fs->PathIsRelative(pPathname))
3109  return fdt->usr_open(pPathname, flags, mode);
3110 
3111  fixme("dirfd=%d is stub", dirfd);
3112  return -linux_ENOSYS;

3115 static long linux_newfstatat(SysFrm *, int dirfd, const char *pathname,
3116  struct linux_kstat *statbuf, int flag)
3117 {
3118  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
3119  vfs::FileDescriptorTable *fdt = pcb->FileDescriptors;
3120  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
3121 
3122  if (flag)
3123  fixme("flag %#x is stub", flag);

3126  struct linux_kstat *pStatbuf = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(statbuf);
3127  if (pPathname == nullptr || pStatbuf == nullptr)
3128  return -linux_EFAULT;

3130  debug("\"%s\" %#lx %#lx", pPathname, pathname, statbuf);
3131 
3132  if (fs->PathIsAbsolute(pPathname))
3133  {
3134  debug("path \"%s\" is absolute", pPathname);
3135  struct kstat nstat = KStatToStat(*pStatbuf);

3137  *pStatbuf = StatToKStat(nstat);

3165  if (!node)
3166  return -linux_ENOENT;
3167 
3168  struct kstat nstat = {};
3169  int ret = fdt->usr_stat(node->GetPath().c_str(), &nstat);
3170  *pStatbuf = StatToKStat(nstat);

3193 static int linux_prlimit64(SysFrm *, pid_t pid, int resource,
3194  const struct rlimit *new_limit,
3195  struct rlimit *old_limit)
3196 {
3197  static_assert(sizeof(struct rlimit) < PAGE_SIZE);
3198 
3199  PCB *pcb = nullptr;
3200  if (likely(pid == 0))
3201  pcb = thisProcess;
3202  else
3203  {
3204  pcb = thisProcess->GetContext()->GetProcessByID(pid);
3205  if (pcb == nullptr)
3206  return -linux_ESRCH;
3207 
3208  fixme("implement CAP_SYS_RESOURCE");
3209  return -linux_EPERM;
3210  }
3211  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = thisProcess->vma;
3212 
3213  auto pOldLimit = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(old_limit);
3214  auto pNewLimit = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(new_limit);
3215  if (pOldLimit == nullptr && old_limit != nullptr)
3216  return -linux_EFAULT;
3217 
3218  if (pNewLimit == nullptr && new_limit != nullptr)
3219  return -linux_EFAULT;
3220 
3221  if (new_limit)
3222  {
3223  if (pNewLimit->rlim_cur > pNewLimit->rlim_max)
3224  return -linux_EINVAL;
3225  }
3226 
3227  switch (resource)
3228  {
3229  case linux_RLIMIT_CPU:
3230  case linux_RLIMIT_FSIZE:
3231  case linux_RLIMIT_DATA:
3232  case linux_RLIMIT_STACK:
3233  case linux_RLIMIT_CORE:
3234  case linux_RLIMIT_RSS:
3235  goto __stub;
3236  case linux_RLIMIT_NPROC:
3237  {
3238  if (old_limit)
3239  {
3240  pOldLimit->rlim_cur = pcb->SoftLimits.Threads;
3241  pOldLimit->rlim_max = pcb->HardLimits.Threads;
3242  debug("read NPROC limit: {%#lx, %#lx}", pOldLimit->rlim_cur, pOldLimit->rlim_max);
3243  }
3244 
3245  if (new_limit)
3246  {
3247  if (pNewLimit->rlim_max > pcb->HardLimits.Threads && !pcb->Security.CanAdjustHardLimits)
3248  return -linux_EPERM;
3249 
3250  debug("setting NPROC limit to {%#lx, %#lx}->{%#lx, %#lx}",
3251  pcb->SoftLimits.Threads, pcb->HardLimits.Threads,
3252  pNewLimit->rlim_cur, pNewLimit->rlim_max);
3253  pcb->SoftLimits.Threads = pNewLimit->rlim_cur;
3254  pcb->HardLimits.Threads = pNewLimit->rlim_max;
3255  }
3256  return 0;
3257  }
3258  case linux_RLIMIT_NOFILE:
3259  {
3260  if (old_limit)
3261  {
3262  pOldLimit->rlim_cur = pcb->SoftLimits.OpenFiles;
3263  pOldLimit->rlim_max = pcb->HardLimits.OpenFiles;
3264  debug("read NOFILE limit: {%#lx, %#lx}", pOldLimit->rlim_cur, pOldLimit->rlim_max);
3265  }
3266 
3267  if (new_limit)
3268  {
3269  if (pNewLimit->rlim_max > pcb->HardLimits.OpenFiles && !pcb->Security.CanAdjustHardLimits)
3270  return -linux_EPERM;
3271 
3272  debug("setting NOFILE limit to {%#lx, %#lx}->{%#lx, %#lx}",
3273  pcb->SoftLimits.OpenFiles, pcb->HardLimits.OpenFiles,
3274  pNewLimit->rlim_cur, pNewLimit->rlim_max);
3275  pcb->SoftLimits.OpenFiles = pNewLimit->rlim_cur;
3276  pcb->HardLimits.OpenFiles = pNewLimit->rlim_max;
3277  }
3278  return 0;
3279  }
3280  case linux_RLIMIT_MEMLOCK:
3281  goto __stub;
3282  case linux_RLIMIT_AS:
3283  {
3284  if (old_limit)
3285  {
3286  pOldLimit->rlim_cur = pcb->SoftLimits.Memory;
3287  pOldLimit->rlim_max = pcb->HardLimits.Memory;
3288  debug("read AS limit: {%#lx, %#lx}", pOldLimit->rlim_cur, pOldLimit->rlim_max);
3289  }
3290 
3291  if (new_limit)
3292  {
3293  if (pNewLimit->rlim_max > pcb->HardLimits.Memory && !pcb->Security.CanAdjustHardLimits)
3294  return -linux_EPERM;
3295 
3296  debug("setting AS limit to {%#lx, %#lx}->{%#lx, %#lx}",
3297  pcb->SoftLimits.Memory, pcb->HardLimits.Memory,
3298  pNewLimit->rlim_cur, pNewLimit->rlim_max);
3299  pcb->SoftLimits.Memory = pNewLimit->rlim_cur;
3300  pcb->HardLimits.Memory = pNewLimit->rlim_max;
3301  }
3302  return 0;
3303  }
3304  case linux_RLIMIT_LOCKS:
3305  case linux_RLIMIT_SIGPENDING:
3306  case linux_RLIMIT_MSGQUEUE:
3307  case linux_RLIMIT_NICE:
3308  case linux_RLIMIT_RTPRIO:
3309  case linux_RLIMIT_RTTIME:
3310  case linux_RLIMIT_NLIMITS:
3311  __stub:
3312  {
3313  fixme("resource %s(%d) is stub", rlimitStr[resource], resource);
3314  return 0; /* just return 0 */
3315  }
3316  default:
3317  {
3318  debug("Invalid resource %d", resource);
3319  return -linux_EINVAL;
3320  }
3321  }
3322 }
3323 
3324 static ssize_t linux_getrandom(SysFrm *, void *buf,
3325  size_t buflen, unsigned int flags)
3326 {
3327  PCB *pcb = thisProcess;
3328  Memory::VirtualMemoryArea *vma = pcb->vma;
3329 
3330  if (flags & linux_GRND_NONBLOCK)
3331  fixme("GRND_NONBLOCK not implemented");
3332 
3333  if (flags & ~(linux_GRND_NONBLOCK |
3334  linux_GRND_RANDOM |
3335  linux_GRND_INSECURE))
3336  {
3337  warn("Invalid flags %#x", flags);
3338  return -linux_EINVAL;
3339  }
3340 
3341  auto pBuf = vma->UserCheckAndGetAddress(buf, buflen);
3342  if (pBuf == nullptr)
3343  return -linux_EFAULT;
3344 
3345  if (flags & linux_GRND_RANDOM)
3346  {
3347  uint16_t random;
3348  for (size_t i = 0; i < buflen; i++)
3349  {
3350  random = Random::rand16();
3351  ((uint8_t *)pBuf)[i] = uint8_t(random & 0xFF);
3352  }
3353  return buflen;
3354  }
3355 
3356  return 0;
3357 }

4259 uintptr_t HandleLinuxSyscalls(SyscallsFrame *Frame)
4260 {
4261 #if defined(a64)
4262  if (Frame->rax > sizeof(LinuxSyscallsTableAMD64) / sizeof(SyscallData))
4263  {
4264  fixme("Syscall %d not implemented",
4265  Frame->rax);
4266  return -linux_ENOSYS;
4267  }
4268 
4269  SyscallData Syscall = LinuxSyscallsTableAMD64[Frame->rax];
4270 
4271  long (*call)(SysFrm *, long, ...) = r_cst(long (*)(SysFrm *, long, ...),
4272  Syscall.Handler);
4273 
4274  if (unlikely(!call))
4275  {
4276  fixme("Syscall %s(%d) not implemented",
4277  Syscall.Name, Frame->rax);
4278  return -linux_ENOSYS;
4279  }
4280 
4281  debug("> [%d:\"%s\"]( %#lx %#lx %#lx %#lx %#lx %#lx )",
4282  Frame->rax, Syscall.Name,
4283  Frame->rdi, Frame->rsi, Frame->rdx,
4284  Frame->r10, Frame->r8, Frame->r9);
4285 
4286  long sc_ret = call(Frame,
4287  Frame->rdi, Frame->rsi, Frame->rdx,
4288  Frame->r10, Frame->r8, Frame->r9);
4289 
4290  debug("< [%ld:\"%s\"] = %ld", Frame->rax, Syscall.Name, sc_ret);
4291  return sc_ret;
4292 #elif defined(a32)
4293  if (Frame->eax > sizeof(LinuxSyscallsTableI386) / sizeof(SyscallData))
4294  {
4295  fixme("Syscall %d not implemented",
4296  Frame->eax);
4297  return -linux_ENOSYS;
4298  }
4299 
4300  SyscallData Syscall = LinuxSyscallsTableI386[Frame->eax];
4301 
4302  long (*call)(SysFrm *, long, ...) = r_cst(long (*)(SysFrm *, long, ...),
4303  Syscall.Handler);
4304 
4305  if (unlikely(!call))
4306  {
4307  fixme("Syscall %s(%d) not implemented",
4308  Syscall.Name, Frame->eax);
4309  return -linux_ENOSYS;
4310  }
4311 
4312  debug("> [%d:\"%s\"]( %#lx %#lx %#lx %#lx %#lx %#lx )",
4313  Frame->eax, Syscall.Name,
4314  Frame->ebx, Frame->ecx, Frame->edx,
4315  Frame->esi, Frame->edi, Frame->ebp);
4316 
4317  int sc_ret = call(Frame,
4318  Frame->ebx, Frame->ecx, Frame->edx,
4319  Frame->esi, Frame->edi, Frame->ebp);
4320 
4321  debug("< [%d:\"%s\"] = %d", Frame->eax, Syscall.Name, sc_ret);
4322  return sc_ret;
4323 #elif defined(aa64)
4324  return -linux_ENOSYS;
4325 #endif
4326 
4327 #if defined(a64)
4328  UNUSED(LinuxSyscallsTableI386);
4329 #elif defined(a32)
4330  UNUSED(LinuxSyscallsTableAMD64);
4331 #endif
4332 }
